{
  "level": "A2–C1",
  "intro": "In this section you will fully master the <strong>passive voice</strong> in English: from the basic formation rules to more advanced constructions with infinitives, gerunds, and modal verbs.",
  "rules": [
    {
      "label": "Basics",
      "color": "emerald",
      "text": "The basic structure is: <strong>Subject + be + Past Participle (V3)</strong>:",
      "example": "The cake is baked by my mother."
    },
    {
      "label": "All Tenses",
      "color": "blue",
      "text": "The passive is used in <strong>9 core English tenses</strong>:",
      "example": "Present/Past/Future Simple, Continuous, Perfect"
    },
    {
      "label": "Modals",
      "color": "rose",
      "text": "The passive with <strong>modal verbs</strong>:",
      "example": "This task must be done today."
    },
    {
      "label": "Infinitive & Gerund",
      "color": "amber",
      "text": "Passive forms of the <strong>infinitive and gerund</strong>:",
      "example": "to be done, being done, having been done"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "title": "1. Core rules for forming the passive",
  "intro": "In the passive voice, the subject receives the action instead of performing it:",
  "items": [
    {
      "label": "Active",
      "title": "Active Voice",
      "subtitle": "The subject performs the action: Tom writes letters."
    },
    {
      "label": "Passive",
      "title": "Passive Voice",
      "subtitle": "The subject receives the action: Letters are written by Tom."
    },
    {
      "label": "Formula",
      "title": "be + V3",
      "subtitle": "The verb be in the required tense + Past Participle."
    },
    {
      "label": "Agent",
      "title": "Agent (by)",
      "subtitle": "by + agent is used when it matters who does the action: by Tom."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "title": "2. When do we use the passive?",
  "sections": [
    {
      "label": "Unknown agent",
      "color": "emerald",
      "description": "When the doer of the action is <strong>unknown or unimportant</strong>:",
      "examples": [
        {
          "en": "My bike was stolen yesterday.",
          "ua": "My bike was stolen yesterday."
        },
        {
          "en": "The window has been broken.",
          "ua": "The window has been broken."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "Focus on the action",
      "color": "blue",
      "description": "When the <strong>action itself or its result</strong> is more important than who did it:",
      "examples": [
        {
          "en": "The report was submitted on time.",
          "ua": "The report was submitted on time."
        },
        {
          "en": "English is spoken in many countries.",
          "ua": "English is spoken in many countries."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "Formal style",
      "color": "rose",
      "description": "In <strong>academic, official, and business</strong> communication:",
      "examples": [
        {
          "en": "The experiment was conducted last month.",
          "ua": "The experiment was conducted last month."
        },
        {
          "en": "Applicants will be contacted by email.",
          "ua": "Applicants will be contacted by email."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
